												<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/aditimachado/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/aditi-machado-author-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/aditi-machado-author-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="Aditi Machado" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
												<div class="description author withsidebar">
													<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/aditimachado/">Aditi Machado</a></h6>
													Aditi Machado is a poet, translator, and essayist. Her works include <em>Some Beheadings</em> (2017), a translation from the French of Farid Tali’s <em>Prosopopoeia</em> (2016), and <em>Emporium</em> (2020), a book of poems which received the James Laughlin Award. Machado’s other work appears in journals such as <em>BOMB</em>, <em>The Chicago Review</em>, and <em>Jacket2</em>. She is an Associate Professor of English at the University of Cincinnati.																									</div>
											</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
										</div>

